  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Nam\n        Sibyl...</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>This opening quote from Petronius' <em>Satyricon </em>(1st\n        century A.D.) sets the scene for the poem - the Sibyl is\n        an old, withered, but immortal woman who is tired with\n        life and wants to die; note the similarites with\n        Gerontion, of which more below.</p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Sibyl.htm\"><font>The Cumaean Sibyl</font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"publication_data.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>The Meaning of the Notes</td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Nam Sibyl... This opening quote from Petronius' Satyricon (1st century A.D.) sets the scene for the poem - the Sibyl is an old, withered, but immortal woman who is tired with life and wants to die; note the similarites with Gerontion, of which more below. reference topics The Cumaean Sibyl The Meaning of the Notes back to \"The Waste Land\"",
